# Code Quality Checks - MANDATORY

## 🚨 **CRITICAL RULE**: Always Run Quality Checks After Code Changes

**MANDATORY REQUIREMENT**: After writing or modifying ANY code, you MUST run all three quality checks before considering the work complete.

### ✅ Required Quality Checks (In Order)

#### 1. Lint Check - Code Quality
```bash
pnpm lint
```

**Purpose:**
- Ensures code follows ESLint rules
- Catches common mistakes and anti-patterns
- Maintains consistent code style
- Verifies no unused variables or imports

**When to run:**
- After modifying any `.ts`, `.tsx`, `.js`, `.jsx` files
- Before committing changes
- After adding/removing imports

**Success criteria:**
```
✓ No linting errors
✓ All warnings addressed or documented
```

---

#### 2. Type Check - Type Safety
```bash
pnpm type-check
```

**Purpose:**
- Validates TypeScript types across all packages
- Catches type errors before runtime
- Ensures type-safe integration between components
- Verifies no TypeScript compilation errors

**When to run:**
- After modifying any `.ts` or `.tsx` files
- After changing type definitions or interfaces
- After updating dependencies
- Before committing changes

**Success criteria:**
```
✓ TypeScript compilation successful
✓ No type errors in any package
✓ All type definitions validated
```

---

#### 3. Build - Production Readiness
```bash
pnpm build
```

**Purpose:**
- Verifies code compiles for production
- Catches build-time errors
- Validates Next.js pages and routes
- Ensures production bundle is valid

**When to run:**
- After any code changes
- After modifying component structure
- After changing imports or dependencies
- Before committing changes

**Success criteria:**
```
✓ Production build completed successfully
✓ All pages compile without errors
✓ Bundle sizes are reasonable
✓ No build warnings (or documented)
```

---

## 🔄 Complete Workflow

### Standard Code Change Workflow
```bash
# 1. Make your code changes
[edit files]

# 2. Run quality checks (MANDATORY)
pnpm lint          # ✓ Code quality
pnpm type-check    # ✓ Type safety
pnpm build         # ✓ Production readiness

# 3. Fix any issues that arise
[fix errors if any]

# 4. Re-run checks after fixes
pnpm lint && pnpm type-check && pnpm build

# 5. Only commit when ALL checks pass
git add .
git commit -m "type: description"
git push
```

### Quick Verification Command
```bash
# Run all checks in sequence
pnpm lint && pnpm type-check && pnpm build && echo "✅ ALL QUALITY CHECKS PASSED"
```

