## 🚫 **NEVER Commit Without These Checks**

### ❌ Anti-Patterns (DO NOT DO THIS)

**DON'T skip checks:**
```bash
# ❌ WRONG - Skipping quality checks
git add . && git commit -m "fix: something" && git push
```

**DON'T commit with errors:**
```bash
# ❌ WRONG - Committing with lint errors
pnpm lint  # Shows errors
git commit -m "fix: something anyway"  # NO!
```

**DON'T ignore type errors:**
```bash
# ❌ WRONG - Ignoring TypeScript errors
pnpm type-check  # Shows type errors
# "I'll fix it later" - NO!
```

**DON'T skip build verification:**
```bash
# ❌ WRONG - Not testing production build
pnpm lint ✓
pnpm type-check ✓
git commit -m "done"  # Missing build check!
```

---

### ✅ Correct Patterns (DO THIS)

**Always run all checks:**
```bash
# ✅ CORRECT - Full quality verification
pnpm lint          # Pass ✓
pnpm type-check    # Pass ✓
pnpm build         # Pass ✓
git commit -m "feat: add new feature"
```

**Fix issues immediately:**
```bash
# ✅ CORRECT - Fix errors before committing
pnpm lint          # Shows 2 warnings
[fix warnings]
pnpm lint          # Pass ✓
pnpm type-check    # Pass ✓
pnpm build         # Pass ✓
git commit
```

**Verify after fixes:**
```bash
# ✅ CORRECT - Re-check after fixing
[fix lint error]
pnpm lint && pnpm type-check && pnpm build
# All pass ✓ → Safe to commit
```

